VKalasagaram recently hosted a vocal recital by N. Subba Lakshmi as part of its monthly concert at Key&#8217;s High School. Subba Lakshmi is in a state of transformation as she is slowly shifting her style from fixed notationpaddathitomanodharma sangeetham. Having a goodsruthiand voice, Lakshmi needs to work on her voice modulation.Subba Lakshmi began her recital with Natkuranji Varnam in a steady way and went on to singSwsaminathain Natai with setswaram. Hamsanadam was taken for a detailedalapand the krithiBantureethi Koluvuof Thyagaraja sounded mechanical withswaramat a speedy pace.Nee daya radhain Kalyana Vasantham was a noteworthy presentation. Poorvikalyani was taken for a brief expansion and Thyagaraja&#8217;sGnanamosagaradhain Rupakam was the krithi.Marugela rain Jayanthasree of Thyagaraja was a routine fast number before going for the main ragam Thodi. Thodi is such a ragam where in it is easy to attempt but very difficult to impress.The pakkavadyams sounded loud on the day. Jayabhasker showed his experience on the mridangam with his decent support and his tani with Shyam forara edamin Adi talam was a treat.
